headline: U.S. Cellular’s (NYSE:USM) Q2: Beats On Revenue
summary: Wireless telecommunications provider U.S. Cellular (NYSE:USM) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, but sales fell by 1.2% year on year to $916 million. Its GAAP profit of $0.36 per share was 7.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
